The paper focuses on the application of neuroevolution (NE) in games, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.NE and cs.AI are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the different types of neural networks used, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of fitness functions, which is a concept in game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the input received by the neural networks, which can include visual input, falling under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
